This is my first time rating anything on Google- this is how disturbed I am from this order. I ordered 2 breakfast burritos and it was hands down the worst thing I’ve ever eaten in life. (Love their sandwiches- but mother of god steer clear of the breakfast burritos.) The burrito had NO cheese (a sin of monumental proportions) barely any eggs (why are we here then), but thank god was filled with mostly undercooked/raw potatoes in a huge flour tortilla. So my husband and I legit ate raw potatoes with a flour tortilla for $16 each. I’m already blacking out from the memory. Seamless gave me a refund, and I need to see a therapist after this life altering event.

Fancy grocery store with great food, drinks and coffee in the back! Definitely try the babka menchkins which are the babka version of munchkins and are totally delicious and rich and gooey. Also of note is the cod and caviar baked potato which is perfection for you and all you czar friends. Don't forget to check out the impressive beer selection, you're sure to find someone new and interesting every time you come in.

Food and drinks are SO great.  5 stars,  period.  I'm subtracting one star for the service. The staff are great,  but the systems are lacking.  One time we had dessert served to us 15 minutes before the entrees arrived.  Last night,  the meat plate came 20 minutes after the hot food. Shouldn't that come quickly?  You order at the bar.  There's no waitstaff.  Very efficient for them.  I get that. But someone there needs to realize that,  if a dessert and sandwich are on the same ticket,  they shouldn't start the dessert until they've served the sandwich. The fried chicken sandwich,  duck bahn mi (sp?) And porchetta are all to die for.  And don't miss the "menschkins" (donut holes made from cinnamon babka, rolled in cinnamon and sugar, with a cream cheese frosting dipping sauce... any chance they'll ever make these with chocolate babka?... maybe even more amazing! ). And the music is always very good... very hip.  Recommended highly as a hang,  where you'll linger with friends and not worry too much about when and the order the food is served in.  Pro tip?  Don't order dessert until your entrees have been served.

Least accommodating store, wonder how long they will last in this neighborhood.  The store has window service to get coffee for people with dogs since they are not allowed in due to health code (understandable) However, the window was closed due to wind and I popped in and told them I had a small dog and they told me to tie him up outside.. mind you he's a small 7lb chihuahua and it's 35 degrees outside. The proper response would have been to ask what I'd like and ask me to step out with the dog, not leave him alone outside. teach your workers proper customer service and empathy.
Awsome gourmet market the best in Williamsburg i love the chocolate bread

The food here is nothing short of amazing.. I say a Brooklyn gem as it is such a unique design.. Corner store with a deli,  I know you're bored reading this, but wait...... theres and awesome bar and kitchen in the back!!! The baked potato with caviar on top is my go to, must have.... My wife's mac and cheese I suspect will be her go to... the beer selection is as amazing as the food.

Walked in and found an amazing bar in the back with a vast selection of gourmet menu items, and over 20 beers on tap. The bartenders let me sample their favorite drafts at the bar before I settled on the Grimm Babka Stout. A babka infused beer! Heaven. Great bar food and atmosphere. When the sun goes down the bar has that perfect “light enough to eat, dark enough to drink” feel.  Don’t let the grocery in the front fool you, this place has a lot going on. From coffee to chicken sandwiches at 2 am.  Staff is friendly and welcoming.
Great service and food was phenomenal

Never mind comfort food, how about comfort Beer?  We cannot say enough about how good it is and a great anchor for this newly developing community. Whether you grab and go in the morning on the way to the new E River Ferry,  or entering the new skate Park or just taking in the view, it is Mekelburg’s for food and comfort. Gooooooo!!
Brilliant. Incredible beer list, tasty food, great service. Not to mention the grocery selection.

I love Mekelburg's Domino. The grocery in front is terrific with it's high quality produce, things like olive oils and vinegars, and cheeses. But it's the bar in back that I enjoy most. There are an enormous number of craft beers on tap and in cans that continually change. And there are cocktails.  The bar also has fabulous food. It's not that it's a restaurant exactly but then it's not that it isn't a restaurant. Maybe the bar just has really high end bar food by which I mean a selection of wonderful sandwiches, like the porchetta or the meatloaf or the vegetarian or the roast beef ( you get the idea), or the seasonal soup (I love their butternut squash-apple soup) or the oysters, or their breakfast babka French toast.  And I love the casual atmosphere and the friendly staff.  The last time I went, by the way, I took the ferry from the East 34th ferry terminal to the South Williamsburg terminal after which it was about a 5 or 6 block walk. It's a really easy way to get there.  So, do I love it? I guess I do.

What a spot! A tower of chocolate babkas to eat, a chocolate babka stout to drink at the bar, a slammin hot chicken sammy, and about a million other delicious things to eat and drink. A spacious bar with plenty of seating, a ton of beers and spirits to choose from, prepared foods, amazing cheeses and meats,and a friendly knowledgeable staff. Mekelburg’s Dominoe gets the 2 thumbs up recommendation without a doubt. Did I mention hot chicken????
This place is great. A bar right across from domino park with the best food and a great bar. Service is awesome. I would live in the bar if I could.

At Mekelburg Dominos last night.  Nana's Meatloaf delicious.  Their bar has an incredible assortment of beers on tap as well as liquors.  Took the NYC Ferry to South Williamsburg.  A clear beautiful night.  Going back soon to enjoy the other edibles on the menu.
Everything we ate was delicious! The prep is so great that my husband who doesn't like anything with fish, loved the whitefish crostini. And the beer selection at the bar is any beer lovers paradise.
Best Sandwiches in NYC. Best Beer selection. Go late and get the hot fried chicken sandwich.

Hard to overstate just how great this place is. Top notch beer selection. Incredible food. And the owners and staff are beyond friendly. Great for a meal, a beer, or some awesome prepared foods. Fantastic addition to the neighborhood.

This is a new outpost of the already outstanding Mekelburgs. In the front, there is a great grocery store with fresh fruits and vegetables along with killer meat and cheese cases for all you party or personal needs. The now also have a beer fridge for great cans and bottles to go and a coffee window. Both excellent additions. They also have other merchandise like hot sauce, snacks & chips, pasta, and coffee. After you make your way through the front you will find an amazing beer bar with 20 beers on tap and more cans than you could ever dream of! At the bar, you can also sample their menu of sandwiches and hot and cold plates. The Italian is a good start, then the classic porchetta, duck duck banh mi, and Nonna's meatloaf along with the Mek 'n cheese. You could spend hours and hours at this bar. The staff is wonderful and friendly and quick to recommend a beer and help you settle in for a fun night! Go there. Go there now!
A much larger version of the original Mekelburg’s. Great selection of beers on tap (four more taps here than at the original location!) and the same great food is being served here.
Nice addition to the area. Great for a quick and easy bite, or takeout for a picnic across the street.

Mekelburg's is open for business!  Coffee shop + gourmet grocer + restaurant/bar next to the new waterfront promenade.  I had their classic hot chicken yesterday (delicious!) and this new location has an expanded beer-to-go section.  Update 2018-10-19 The bar has 20 beer taps plus a long list of cans.  The bartenders are very knowledgeable and will recommend beers specifically for you if you ask for advice.  Last night we tried the shrimp poboy and duck banh mi sandwiches - the food is consistently top-notch.
Great beer list. Solid food options.
